# NOT EXECUTABLE — parked follow-up slice (slice 2). The .feature.draft suffix
# keeps these scenarios out of every *.feature glob and the acceptance runner
# (specs/pipeline/runtime.js), so they cannot hard-fail the hardener's gate
# before their step handlers exist (BL-233 slice-scoping). Promote each scenario
# into the live BL-425 .feature file only when slice 2 is actually built.
#
# Slice 2 — SCOPED ANSWER-BACK. Slice 1 (the live feature) is inbound-only: the
# human steers, the agent hears it, but nothing flows back to Telegram. This
# slice adds the return channel the human asked for: the agent's ANSWER to a
# steering message is posted back into that role's steering topic — and ONLY the
# answer, never the agent's ordinary business-as-usual activity. The sanctioned
# design (do not over-prescribe in the scenarios) reuses the operator ask/await +
# reply-relay path (BL-306; operator_reply.bb): the steer is injected wrapped so
# the agent replies through the reply path, which posts to the topic; BAU never
# calls that path, so BAU never reaches the topic.

Feature: an agent's answer to a Telegram steer flows back to its topic, not its activity

  Background:
    Given a running swarm with per-agent steering topics and the authorised human

  # BL-425 answer-back-to-steering-topic-06
  Scenario: an agent's answer to a steer is posted back into that role's topic
    Given the authorised human has steered the "coder" role via its steering topic
    When the "coder" role answers that steer
    Then the answer is posted back into the "coder" role's steering topic

  # BL-425 answer-back-excludes-bau-07
  Scenario: an agent's ordinary activity is not posted to its steering topic
    Given the "coder" role is doing ordinary pipeline work with no pending steer to answer
    When the "coder" role produces its normal pane activity
    Then nothing is posted to the "coder" role's steering topic
